So what is HRV?
HRV is a measure of your autonomic nervous system that is widely considered one of the best objective metrics for physical fitness and determining your body’s readiness to perform.

Although HRV manifests as a function of your heart rate, it actually originates from your nervous system. Your autonomic nervous system, which controls the involuntary aspects of your physiology, has two branches, parasympathetic (deactivating) and sympathetic (activating).

The parasympathetic branch (often referred to as “rest and digest”) handles inputs from internal organs, like digestion or your fingernails and hair growing. It causes a decrease in heart rate.

The sympathetic branch (often called “fight or flight”) reflects responses to things like stress and exercise, and increases your heart rate.

Heart rate variability comes from these two competing branches simultaneously sending signals to your heart. If your nervous system is balanced, your heart is constantly being told to beat slower by your parasympathetic system, and beat faster by your sympathetic system. This causes a fluctuation in your heart rate: HRV.

La asistencia o atención médica remota puede ser a través de cualquier dispositivo móvil con acceso a internet.

E-Nabız, sağlık tesislerinden toplanan kişisel sağlık verilerine, vatandaşların ve vatandaşların yetkilendirdiği yakınlarının ve hekimlerin, internet ve mobil cihazlar üzerinden erişebilecekleri bir uygulamadır.

E-Nabız’da bulunan sağlık bilgileri, sistemin devreye alınmasından itibaren hastalıklarınızla ilgili konulan teşhislerin, yaptırılan tahlillerin, çekimi yapılan tıbbi görüntülerin, yazılan ilaçların, aşıların, tespit edilen alerji ve benzeri bilgilerin sağlık hizmeti alınan sağlık kuruluşları tarafından elektronik ortamda e-Nabız sistemine gönderilmesi ile oluşmaktadır.

Uygulamayı kullanabilmeniz için "https://www.enabiz.gov.tr" sitesinde yer alan "E-Devlet ile Giriş" sekmesinden giriş yaparak e-Nabız sistemini aktif etmeniz gerekmektedir. Kullanıcı onay verdiği takdirde destekleyen mobil cihazlardan ilgili bilgiler uygulama tarafından kullanılacaktır.

Cihazınızda bulunan Sağlık Uygulamasına erişime izin vererek, sağlık verileriniz sisteme gönderilmesini sağlayabilir ve dilediğinizde uygulama içerisinden doktorunuz ile paylaşabilirsiniz.

Vetpocket™ is the #1 Veterinary Professional! Remove the stress and potential errors from complex medical calculations. This must-have tool is used daily by thousands of veterinary professionals and students. Get access to everything you need to have, in your pocket, at all time!

DRUG CALCULATOR
Calculate drug dose and dosages instantly! Create your own personalized drug list with the ability to add an unlimited amount of drugs into the “My Drugs” category, or use our pre-filled ones. We’ve handpicked some of the most commonly used drugs in veterinary medicine, and organized them into 13 categories: Anesthesia & Analgesia, Antibiotics, Antidiarrheals, Antiemetics, Antifungals, Antihistamines, Cardiovascular, Emergency, Gastroprotectants, Neurology, Prednisone, Respiratory and Reversal Agents. You can easily edit any of them to match your practice standards or your personal preference. Any changes you make can be also be restore to our default value at any time.

Drugs can be added or edited using the following fields: Name, Description, Species (20+ species to choose from), Dose and Dosage (fixed and range options to choose from), Concentration (for liquid drugs), Frequency, Tapering (add unlimited taper dosages), Routes (IV, PO, IM and SC), Personal Notes. Make any drug a favorite so it can be easily seen by getting pushed to the top of the list. The search bar allows you to find drugs in seconds.

BASIC CALCULATOR
Our built-in calculator includes an x^0.75 button for easier Fluid and Energy Requirement calculations when using formulas that utilize x^0.75!
